column5: Hi All  Spent Sunday fishing for carp with a buddy and boy did they cooperate! We started at about 8am and the bite didn't slow down until about 5pm but  we were both carped out by then.  :lol: I landed 18 and lost 3, all good size, with my buddy not far behind. The weather wasn't the greatest  (cloudy and windy) but the fish didn't seem to mind. Cheap way to spend a fun day(2 cans of Mr. Goudas corn and a 10 min drive from home).  Here's a couple of pics.
awesome. Thatnks for fix,n the problem.LOL
I bet that the OFC teams just got goosed !  18 carp + 99cents of corn + 10 minute drive = cannot ask for any better than that...you guys rock.
wow what a great action-packed day! WTG guys!
Hey I know that spot! Can't beat urban fishing.
Definitely lots of action for you on this trip. Excellent.
those r actually nice looking carp there specially first and second one  WTG
Carp porn, the best there is ..  thanks for sharing.. great picts.

Great report, nice pics! Thanks for that... but the dude holding them carp close to his chest is gonna have problems with; - any future female attraction! -cleaning bill -smelling like Kensington Market on a nice July day! HH
Ya, I was actually laughing at him until I realized it was my jacket he was wearing.
